cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.AI

This paper deals with the problem of optimizing sensing schedules in dynamic spectrum access networks, which is a topic related to networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) since the authors propose several sensing strategies to optimize system performance. However, since the paper focuses on cooperative spectrum sensing, which is a key feature of cognitive radio networks, cs.NI is the most likely category.
